\end{itemize}



Computer-aided Pronunciation Training (\textbf{CAPT}) technologies play a pivotal role in promoting self-directed language learning, offering learners constant access and tailored feedback. These technologies serve as a valuable adjunct to traditional instruction, effectively addressing the needs of an expanding learner population in a scarcity of qualified teachers \cite{CAPT_2, CAPT}. These systems generally operate by capturing the learner's speech, identifying and analyzing any mispronunciations present, and providing appropriate corrective suggestions. For example, let's say a learner mispronounces the word `lamb' as /l ae n/ (`lane'). The CAPT system should be able to respond by pointing out the error: "You mispronounced the the phone /m/ as /n/. Try to press your lips together towards the end of the word." 

